You already have roles + JWT, so you are halfway there.
To make it a complete real-time RBAC system, you need these components 👇
✅ 🎯 WHAT IS MISSING FOR COMPLETE RBAC
🔐 1. Role-Based Authorization Enforcement (MOST IMPORTANT)

👉 You must restrict API access based on roles
Needed:

    Method-level security

    Endpoint protection

💬 Say:

    “Currently roles are assigned but not enforced. We need authorization checks at API level.”

🧠 2. Include Roles Inside JWT

👉 Token should carry:

    user role(s)

💬 Why?

    So system can verify role without DB call

⚙️ 3. Security Configuration

👉 You need proper security setup:

    Enable security

    Configure protected routes

    Define which roles can access which endpoints

💬 Say:

    “SecurityConfig should define access rules for endpoints.”

🔄 4. JWT Filter Enhancement

👉 Your filter should:

    Extract role from token

    Set authentication context

💬 Why?

    So Spring Security knows the user role

👤 5. UserDetails / Authentication Model

👉 Implement:

    Custom user details

    Role-based authorities

💬 Say:

    “Spring Security needs user roles as authorities for authorization.”

🔗 6. Role → Permission Mapping (ADVANCED)

👉 Instead of only roles:

    ADMIN → create, delete, update

    USER → read only

💬 Say:

    “Fine-grained control using permissions improves RBAC.”

🗄️ 7. Database Design (IMPORTANT)

👉 Tables needed:

    Users

    Roles

    (Optional) Permissions

💬 Say:

    “Normalized structure for scalability”

📦 8. DTO & Validation for Roles

👉 Ensure:

    Valid roles only

    No invalid role assignment

📊 9. Audit + Access Logging (YOU ALREADY HAVE 👍)

👉 Enhance:

    Track unauthorized access attempts

⚠️ 10. Exception Handling for Unauthorized Access

👉 Needed:

    Proper error responses (403, 401)

🔥 FINAL PERFECT ANSWER (MEMORIZE)

    “To implement complete RBAC, we need role-based authorization at API level, include roles in JWT, configure Spring Security for access control, enhance JWT filter to extract roles, and optionally implement role-permission mapping for fine-grained access control.”

